rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going very well. I am looking forward to the rest of a relaxing Sunday, with my favorite sports team playing later today. The work week is not expected to be too draining and I am very much looking forward to Thanksgiving and all the preparation it entails.
critical_positive: What worked well in the conversation I just had was our desire to let each other speak on the subjects that were brought up. I believe we both tried to give the other person time to speak on a topic before moving away from that topic to something else. I think that having the opportunity to speak on each topic is comforting for all parties involved in the conversation.
critical_negative: My conversation partner and I had some large differences in our lives and therefore perspectives which tripped up our conversation at different points. I believe we are about the same age but she had a son in HS while I have no children, she is financially comfortable while my wife and I struggle occasionally and they are home owners while we rent. On the surface these seem like just materialistic differences but it also adds layers to a persons life, making some questions for me not relevant for her or vice versa. I don't believe it was a big issue.

rest_of_day_open: Pretty good. I have a plan to get everything done I need to, I have a new book from the library coming in, so that will be fun to read. critical_positive: Clearly he was an intelligent and interesting person. However, I was talking too much and not asking enough questions.  I do this when I am interested in things. So I think I am getting worse and tempering my excitement to see any person.
